    "description": {
      "value": "<p><em style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;color:#191813;font-size:13px\">This is an optional class feature. Consult with your DM before adding this to your character.</em></p>\n<p>At 2nd level, you gain the ability to summon a spirit that assumes an animal form: as an action, you can expend a use of your @Compendium[5e-complete.5e-class-features.jXMI4Iy8McDpVl5y]{Wild Shape} feature to cast the @Compendium[5e-complete.5e-spells.XcOo5GgPPQZ2PJ0C]{Find Familiar} spell, without material components.</p>\n<p>When you cast the spell in this way, the familiar is a fey instead of a beast, and the familiar disappears after a number of hours equal to half your druid level.</p>",
